## Input
```python
# Nested string literals inside t-string expressions follow either alternating
# or preferred quote normalization depending on nested-string-quote-style.
t'{ "nested" }'
t'{ "nested" = }'
t'{ ["1", "2"] }'
```

## Outputs
### Output 1
```
indent-style               = space
line-width                 = 88
indent-width               = 4
quote-style                = Double
line-ending                = LineFeed
magic-trailing-comma       = Respect
docstring-code             = Disabled
docstring-code-line-width  = "dynamic"
preview                    = Disabled
target_version             = 3.14
source_type                = Python
nested-string-quote-style  = alternating
```

```python
# Nested string literals inside t-string expressions follow either alternating
# or preferred quote normalization depending on nested-string-quote-style.
t"{'nested'}"
t"{ "nested" = }"
t"{['1', '2']}"
```


### Output 2
```
indent-style               = space
line-width                 = 88
indent-width               = 4
quote-style                = Double
line-ending                = LineFeed
magic-trailing-comma       = Respect
docstring-code             = Disabled
docstring-code-line-width  = "dynamic"
preview                    = Disabled
target_version             = 3.14
source_type                = Python
nested-string-quote-style  = preferred
```

```python
# Nested string literals inside t-string expressions follow either alternating
# or preferred quote normalization depending on nested-string-quote-style.
t"{"nested"}"
t"{ "nested" = }"
t"{["1", "2"]}"
```
